results.name: a(n) = d(n+d(n)), where d(n) is the number of divisors of n (A000005).
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
Aleksandar Ivić, An asymptotic formula involving the enumerating function of finite Abelian groups, Publikacije Elektrotehničkog fakulteta, Serija Matematika 3 (1992), pp. 61-66.
Imre Kátai, On a problem of A. Ivic, Mathematica Pannonica, Vol. 18, No. 1 (2007), pp. 11-18.
formula: Sum_{k=1..n} a(k) ~ D*n*log(n) + O(n*log(n)/log(log(n))), where D > 0 is a constant (conjectured with an error O(n) by Ivić, 1992; proven by Kátai, 2007). - _Amiram Eldar_, Jul 08 2020
